This Unicode icon is suitable for indicating the direction of movement or wind, the parts of the world (south, north, etc.), transition, transformation. In mathematics and logic, similar symbols denote an implication, a limit, a vector, and in chemistry - one-way chemical reactions. The symbol is suitable for creating navigation signs and diagrams at airports, shopping malls and other places with a large flow of visitors.

In addition to Heavy Wide-Headed Rightwards Arrow, there are other similar symbols in Unicode. Among them are [U:2192], [U:27F6], [U:21D2]. The arrows vary in size, line thickness, and other parameters. Most of them may be used both as an icon for writing formulas, and for decorating diagrams, lists and other text elements.
